    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-03-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-03-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="241"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 283/61–64.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 20, 1907</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 15.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note No. 16, of the 13th instant, stating that the smuggling of
                    arms and ammunition from Arizona, for the use of the Yaqui Indians, has been
                    resumed, and requesting the cooperation of this Government to put a stop
                    thereto.</p>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that copies of your note and of its
                    inclosures have been sent to the governor of Arizona, the Secretaries of War, of
                    the Treasury, and of Commerce and Labor, and to the Attorney-General, with the
                    request that they again put into operation the precautionary measures employed
                    by them last summer to prevent arms and ammunition from reaching these
                    rebellious Indians.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
